{"title_page": "Anshuman Tiwari", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Other people|Anshuman|Anshuman (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Indian journalist}}\n\n{{Infobox writer\n|name           = Anshuman  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/tiwarianshuman |title=Anshuman , Editor \u2013 India Today (Hindi)}}</ref>\n|image          = Anshuman Tiwari.jpg\n|image         = Anshuman Tiwari Official.jpg\n|alt            = Photo of Anshuman \n|caption        =\n|birth_date     = \n|birth_place    = [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n|occupation     = Editor, [[journalist]]\n|education      = [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]], [[Master of Arts|MA]] (double), Master's Diploma in Mass Communication and Journalism\n|awards         = * Fellow of prestigious Chevening Fellowship (2017) of Government of United Kingdom. Studied at [[University of Westminster]] and presented paper on how media houses grappling with online comments in different parts of the world. Also worked with Financial Times London as part of field work under fellowship.<ref name=\"chevening\" />\n* India's top blogger: Arthaat, weekly blog in politics and economy was honoured as one of the India's most read in 2016<ref name=\"bestblogs\" />\n* Ramnath Goenka Award for Investigative Journalism<ref name=\"goenka\" />\n* WAN-IFRA International Award for Breaking News<ref name=\"wanifra\" />\n|years_active   = 1991\u2013present\n|spouse         = \n|children       = \n|alma_mater     = [[University]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n|website        = {{url|artharthanshuman.blogspot.in}}\n}}\n\n'''Anshuman Tiwari''' (born 25 March 1974) is an [[editor]] of ''[[India Today]]'' (Hindi)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/author/Anshuman-Tiwari/1.html | title=Anshuman Tiwari Editor of India Today Hindi}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html|title=Anshuman Tiwari, Editor of India Today (Hindi)}}</ref> at ''[[India Today Group]]'' in [[New Delhi]]. He is a former Chief of National Bureau and Associate Editor<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms|title=Anshuman Tiwari Chief of National Bureau and Associate Editor}}</ref> of ''[[Dainik Jagran]]''. He is Chevening Fellow of South Asia Journalism Program 2017.<ref name=\"chevening\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chevening.org/fellows/sajp-fellows-0 | title=Fellow of prestigious Chevening Fellowship (2017) of Government of United Kingdom}}</ref>\n\nHe has also been a fellow of the [[International Center for Journalists]] (ICFJ),<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.icfj.org/participants | title=Fellow of International Center for Journalists (ICFJ)}}</ref> UK financial sector study, European Union and US International Visitor Program.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} He has worked with ''[[Financial Times]]'' London and ''Dayton News Chronicle'', Ohio as a part of international training.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\nHe is an accomplished multimedia economic/political [[journalist]], [[Policy analysis|analyst]], [[researcher]] and [[columnist]] in English and Hindi languages with 25 years of media experience in various capacities across leading Hindi dailies, digital news ventures and magazine.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms | title=Dainik Jagran chief of national bureau }}</ref> He has been named one of the top 50 most prominent Hindi journalists in India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html | title=Veteran journalist Anshuman Tiwari to be new Editor of India Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://tennews.in/national-health-editors-meet-on-routine-immunization/ | title=Top 50 most prominent Hindi journalists in India}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 September 2017, his blog Arthaat was listed in the directory of \"Best Hindi Blog\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantopblogs.com/p/hindi-blog-directory.html |title=Directory of Best Hindi Blogs}}</ref> which is released by ITB.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantopblogs.com/2017/09/best-of-hindi-blogging-2017.html |title=Releasing the 2017 edition of Best Hindi Blog Directory }}</ref> In 2017, it was re-listed as best [[Hindi]] blog for the third time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://samachar4media.com/arthaat-blog-has-been-listed-in-2017-edition-of-best-hindi-blogs-directory |title=Anshuman Tiwari's blog editor of 'India Today' (Hindi) got different identity}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nAnshuman Tiwari was born on 25 March 1974<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/tiwarianshuman |title=Anshuman Tiwari born in 1974}}</ref> in Uttar Pradesh, [[India]]. He graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Hindi/English literature, Geography in 1988 from Kannauj, Uttar Pradesh, and got a master's degree as Master of Arts (double), Geography and Hindi Literature  from [[Kanpur]], Uttar Pradesh in 1990 with a professional degree in Master's Diploma in Mass communication and Journalism  in 1991 from Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Kanpur.\n\nHe joined the most prestigious and largest news magazine, ''[[India Today]]'', [[Aaj Tak]] Group as an editor in New Delhi, India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://aajtak.intoday.in/ |title=India Today, Aaj Tak Group}}</ref> Previously, he was Chief of National Bureau / Chief of Bureaus / Group Input Head and Associate Editor for ''Dainik Jagran'' (India's largest Hindi daily) from 2008 to 2013. He led www.money.bhaskar.com<ref>[http://money.bhaskar.com/ www.money.bhaskar.com]</ref> (a digital first Hindi economic content vertical belonging to DB Corp, India second largest media conglomerate) as an editor and Vertical Head.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://money.bhaskar.com |title=Business News Daily Hindi}}</ref>\n\nHe is a regular [[columnist]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyo.in/user/3270/anshuman1tiwari|title=Anshuman Tiwari as Columnist for Dailyo}}</ref> for the daily news portal Daliyo (India Today group's) in English language.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyo.in/|title=Columnist in Daily News portal}}</ref> As a columnist in Hindi language he wrote in weekly column Artharth/Arthaat, published in ''Dainik Jagran'' for 15 years. It is now published in a weekly feature of ''India Today''.\n\nHe is well known as an economic analyst and journalist. He started his career as stock market correspondent at Kanpur in the early 90s. He covered various economic ministries and reported on macroeconomic, trade and financial markets in varied templates during the length of his career from correspondent to editor.\n\nHe is a distinguished investigative journalist with several far-reaching news scoops to his credit, including a three years long expos\u00e9 of Delhi CWG [[Commonwealth Games]] 2012 in the position of Chief of National Bureau \u2013 ''Dainik Jagran''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms|title=Anshuman Tiwari Chief of National Bureau}}</ref> (November 1995 to February 2014).\n\nIn digital journalism, he has created and successfully established an innovative and exclusive multilingual digital first content vertical moneybhaskar.com for Danik Bhaskar Group,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/ |title=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref> DB Corp.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bhaskarnet.com/ |title=DB Crop}}</ref> It is the largest Hindi business portal and offers guidance, utility and wisdom based jargon free economic-business and investment content to aspiring readers in Hindi. Also he initiated, planned and successfully executed the digital transition of ''Dainik Jagran''.\n\nHe is a researcher and analyst, and has presented quite a few papers at national and global fora. He regularly participates in academic workshops and seminars.\n\nOn 3 November 2018, he  published a book called [[Laxminama]] in New Delhi, India at Indira Gandhi National Center for the Art. The book is about monks, merchants, money, and mantra. He launched this book to make people aware of the connection of economy with religion.\n\n==Honours, awards and accolades==\n* Recipient of India's most prestigious Ramnath Goenka Award for investigative journalism<ref name=\"goenka\">{{cite news|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/ramnath-goenka-awards-express-group-honours-the-best-in-indian-journalism/900305/ |title=Ramnath Goenka Award for investigative journalism}}</ref>\n* Recipient of WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news<ref name=\"wanifra\">{{cite news|url=http://www.wan-ifra.org/articles/2011/04/28/asian-media-award-2011-winners |title=WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news}}</ref>\n* US Elections 2012 Visiting Journalist Program November 2012 \u2013 Only journalist selected from India to cover US president elections for a full month. Worked with ''Dayton News'' in Ohio (US) and covered the election for print, web and social media.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.icfj.org/our-work/elections-2012-visiting-journalists-program | title=US Elections 2012 Visiting Journalist Program November 2012}}</ref>\n* WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news June 2011 \u2013 A World Association of Newspapers award, the first for any Hindi newspaper. The awarded story was an expos\u00e9 of a complimentary ticket scam in Delhi Commonwealth Games 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wan-ifra.org/articles/2011/04/28/asian-media-award-2011-winners | title=WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news June 2011}}</ref>\n* Alumnus of US international visitor's program, first Hindi business journalist invited by the government on a one-month study tour under international visitors' program, April 1999\n* Among top 50 most prominent journalists in India as per the recent survey conducted by the Ace media research firm, Exchange4media<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html | title=Top 50 most prominent journalists in India}}</ref>\n* Uttar Pradesh Hindi Sahitya Sammelan Award 2013 \u2013 award for contribution in Hindi journalism\n* KCK Journalism International award 2009 \u2013 Rajsthan Patrika newspaper group, a prestigious international award for special news series on financing of terror in India <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/hindustan-times-dawn-jointly-conferred-kck-award-2007-for-excellence-in-print-journalism_30154.html | title=KCK Journalism International award 2009}}</ref>\n* Rashtriya Arthik Hindi Patrakarita Purskar 2007 Banaras Beads limited Varanasi National award for Economic Journalism in Hindi<ref>{{cite news|url=http://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1300530.cms | title=Rashtriya Arthik Hindi Patrakarita Purskar 2007}}</ref>\n* India's top blogger. Arthaat, a weekly blog in politics and economy, is honoured as one of India's most read in 2016. This ranking is done by the top Indian website on blogging.<ref name=\"bestblogs\">{{cite news|url=http://samachar4media.com/list-of-best-hindi-blogs | title=\u091f\u0949\u092a \u092c\u094d\u0932\u0949\u0917\u094d\u0938 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 \u0939\u0941\u0906 \u0907\u0938 \u0935\u0930\u093f\u0937\u094d\u0920 \u092a\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0915\u093e\u0930 \u0914\u0930 \u0938\u0902\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0915 \u0915\u093e \u0932\u094b\u0915\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f \u092c\u094d\u0932\u0949\u0917 2015\u20132016}}</ref>\n\n==Books and publications==\n\n* Research paper on the conundrum of online comments, ''How to get most out of wise crowd'', from [[University of Westminster]] under Chevening Fellowship<ref name=\"chevening\" /> \n* Paper on terrorism and economy, published from Calcutta University\n* Paper \u2013 ''Economic Impact of Terror on South Asia''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://iprovok.com/bomb-and-the-bill-economic-impact-of-terrorism/ | title=Economic Impact of Terrorism: Case of South Asia Post 9/11}}</ref>\n* Paper on India and China relations published from ISAS Singapore; profile carried in the collection of seminal papers<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newasiabooks.org/publication/media-work-china-and-india-discovering-and-dissecting | title=India and China relations published from ISAS Singapore}}</ref>\n* Collection of columns published in Hindi\n* Book on India's economic history is in process\n* Laxminama \u2013 Book launched in November 2018\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html Veteran journalist Anshuman Tiwari to be new Editor of India Today (Hindi)- Author, Abhishek Mehrotra, Friday, 1 August 2014]\n* [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms Dainik Jagran chief of national bureau Anshuman Tiwari says that there is need for strong regulation for corporate governance not broadcast regulation]\n* [http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/black-money-narendra-modi-tax-department-foreign-income/1/430551.html Dangers of tax terrorism]\n* {{LinkedIn URL|https://www.linkedin.com/in/tiwarianshuman}}\n* [http://www.dailyo.in/user/3270/anshuman1tiwari Columnist for Dailyo]\n* [http://www.indiantopblogs.com/ Ranking done for the India's top and most read 130 Hindi Blogs for 2015\u20132016]\n* [http://samachar4media.com/list-of-best-hindi-blogs List of best Hindi Blogs 2015\u20132016]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tiwari, Anshuman}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Journalists from Uttar Pradesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Other people|Anshuman|Anshuman (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Indian journalist}}\n\n{{Infobox writer\n|name           = Anshuman  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/tiwarianshuman |title=Anshuman , Editor \u2013 India Today (Hindi)}}</ref>\n|image          = Anshuman Tiwari.jpg\n|alt            = Photo of Anshuman \n|caption        =\n|birth_date     = \n|birth_place    = [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n|occupation     = Editor, [[journalist]]\n|education      = [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]], [[Master of Arts|MA]] (double), Master's Diploma in Mass Communication and Journalism\n|awards         = * Fellow of prestigious Chevening Fellowship (2017) of Government of United Kingdom. Studied at [[University of Westminster]] and presented paper on how media houses grappling with online comments in different parts of the world. Also worked with Financial Times London as part of field work under fellowship.<ref name=\"chevening\" />\n* India's top blogger: Arthaat, weekly blog in politics and economy was honoured as one of the India's most read in 2016<ref name=\"bestblogs\" />\n* Ramnath Goenka Award for Investigative Journalism<ref name=\"goenka\" />\n* WAN-IFRA International Award for Breaking News<ref name=\"wanifra\" />\n|years_active   = 1991\u2013present\n|spouse         = \n|children       = \n|alma_mater     = [[University]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n|website        = {{url|artharthanshuman.blogspot.in}}\n}}\n\n'''Anshuman Tiwari''' (born 25 March 1974) is an [[editor]] of ''[[India Today]]'' (Hindi)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/author/Anshuman-Tiwari/1.html | title=Anshuman Tiwari Editor of India Today Hindi}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html|title=Anshuman Tiwari, Editor of India Today (Hindi)}}</ref> at ''[[India Today Group]]'' in [[New Delhi]]. He is a former Chief of National Bureau and Associate Editor<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms|title=Anshuman Tiwari Chief of National Bureau and Associate Editor}}</ref> of ''[[Dainik Jagran]]''. He is Chevening Fellow of South Asia Journalism Program 2017.<ref name=\"chevening\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chevening.org/fellows/sajp-fellows-0 | title=Fellow of prestigious Chevening Fellowship (2017) of Government of United Kingdom}}</ref>\n\nHe has also been a fellow of the [[International Center for Journalists]] (ICFJ),<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.icfj.org/participants | title=Fellow of International Center for Journalists (ICFJ)}}</ref> UK financial sector study, European Union and US International Visitor Program.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} He has worked with ''[[Financial Times]]'' London and ''Dayton News Chronicle'', Ohio as a part of international training.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}\n\nHe is an accomplished multimedia economic/political [[journalist]], [[Policy analysis|analyst]], [[researcher]] and [[columnist]] in English and Hindi languages with 25 years of media experience in various capacities across leading Hindi dailies, digital news ventures and magazine.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms | title=Dainik Jagran chief of national bureau }}</ref> He has been named one of the top 50 most prominent Hindi journalists in India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html | title=Veteran journalist Anshuman Tiwari to be new Editor of India Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://tennews.in/national-health-editors-meet-on-routine-immunization/ | title=Top 50 most prominent Hindi journalists in India}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 September 2017, his blog Arthaat was listed in the directory of \"Best Hindi Blog\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantopblogs.com/p/hindi-blog-directory.html |title=Directory of Best Hindi Blogs}}</ref> which is released by ITB.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantopblogs.com/2017/09/best-of-hindi-blogging-2017.html |title=Releasing the 2017 edition of Best Hindi Blog Directory }}</ref> In 2017, it was re-listed as best [[Hindi]] blog for the third time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://samachar4media.com/arthaat-blog-has-been-listed-in-2017-edition-of-best-hindi-blogs-directory |title=Anshuman Tiwari's blog editor of 'India Today' (Hindi) got different identity}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nAnshuman Tiwari was born on 25 March 1974<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/tiwarianshuman |title=Anshuman Tiwari born in 1974}}</ref> in Uttar Pradesh, [[India]]. He graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Hindi/English literature, Geography in 1988 from Kannauj, Uttar Pradesh, and got a master's degree as Master of Arts (double), Geography and Hindi Literature  from [[Kanpur]], Uttar Pradesh in 1990 with a professional degree in Master's Diploma in Mass communication and Journalism  in 1991 from Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan, Kanpur.\n\nHe joined the most prestigious and largest news magazine, ''[[India Today]]'', [[Aaj Tak]] Group as an editor in New Delhi, India.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://aajtak.intoday.in/ |title=India Today, Aaj Tak Group}}</ref> Previously, he was Chief of National Bureau / Chief of Bureaus / Group Input Head and Associate Editor for ''Dainik Jagran'' (India's largest Hindi daily) from 2008 to 2013. He led www.money.bhaskar.com<ref>[http://money.bhaskar.com/ www.money.bhaskar.com]</ref> (a digital first Hindi economic content vertical belonging to DB Corp, India second largest media conglomerate) as an editor and Vertical Head.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://money.bhaskar.com |title=Business News Daily Hindi}}</ref>\n\nHe is a regular [[columnist]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyo.in/user/3270/anshuman1tiwari|title=Anshuman Tiwari as Columnist for Dailyo}}</ref> for the daily news portal Daliyo (India Today group's) in English language.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailyo.in/|title=Columnist in Daily News portal}}</ref> As a columnist in Hindi language he wrote in weekly column Artharth/Arthaat, published in ''Dainik Jagran'' for 15 years. It is now published in a weekly feature of ''India Today''.\n\nHe is well known as an economic analyst and journalist. He started his career as stock market correspondent at Kanpur in the early 90s. He covered various economic ministries and reported on macroeconomic, trade and financial markets in varied templates during the length of his career from correspondent to editor.\n\nHe is a distinguished investigative journalist with several far-reaching news scoops to his credit, including a three years long expos\u00e9 of Delhi CWG [[Commonwealth Games]] 2012 in the position of Chief of National Bureau \u2013 ''Dainik Jagran''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms|title=Anshuman Tiwari Chief of National Bureau}}</ref> (November 1995 to February 2014).\n\nIn digital journalism, he has created and successfully established an innovative and exclusive multilingual digital first content vertical moneybhaskar.com for Danik Bhaskar Group,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/ |title=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref> DB Corp.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bhaskarnet.com/ |title=DB Crop}}</ref> It is the largest Hindi business portal and offers guidance, utility and wisdom based jargon free economic-business and investment content to aspiring readers in Hindi. Also he initiated, planned and successfully executed the digital transition of ''Dainik Jagran''.\n\nHe is a researcher and analyst, and has presented quite a few papers at national and global fora. He regularly participates in academic workshops and seminars.\n\nOn 3 November 2018, he  published a book called [[Laxminama]] in New Delhi, India at Indira Gandhi National Center for the Art. The book is about monks, merchants, money, and mantra. He launched this book to make people aware of the connection of economy with religion.\n\n==Honours, awards and accolades==\n* Recipient of India's most prestigious Ramnath Goenka Award for investigative journalism<ref name=\"goenka\">{{cite news|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/ramnath-goenka-awards-express-group-honours-the-best-in-indian-journalism/900305/ |title=Ramnath Goenka Award for investigative journalism}}</ref>\n* Recipient of WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news<ref name=\"wanifra\">{{cite news|url=http://www.wan-ifra.org/articles/2011/04/28/asian-media-award-2011-winners |title=WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news}}</ref>\n* US Elections 2012 Visiting Journalist Program November 2012 \u2013 Only journalist selected from India to cover US president elections for a full month. Worked with ''Dayton News'' in Ohio (US) and covered the election for print, web and social media.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.icfj.org/our-work/elections-2012-visiting-journalists-program | title=US Elections 2012 Visiting Journalist Program November 2012}}</ref>\n* WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news June 2011 \u2013 A World Association of Newspapers award, the first for any Hindi newspaper. The awarded story was an expos\u00e9 of a complimentary ticket scam in Delhi Commonwealth Games 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wan-ifra.org/articles/2011/04/28/asian-media-award-2011-winners | title=WAN-IFRA International award for breaking news June 2011}}</ref>\n* Alumnus of US international visitor's program, first Hindi business journalist invited by the government on a one-month study tour under international visitors' program, April 1999\n* Among top 50 most prominent journalists in India as per the recent survey conducted by the Ace media research firm, Exchange4media<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html | title=Top 50 most prominent journalists in India}}</ref>\n* Uttar Pradesh Hindi Sahitya Sammelan Award 2013 \u2013 award for contribution in Hindi journalism\n* KCK Journalism International award 2009 \u2013 Rajsthan Patrika newspaper group, a prestigious international award for special news series on financing of terror in India <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.exchange4media.com/print/hindustan-times-dawn-jointly-conferred-kck-award-2007-for-excellence-in-print-journalism_30154.html | title=KCK Journalism International award 2009}}</ref>\n* Rashtriya Arthik Hindi Patrakarita Purskar 2007 Banaras Beads limited Varanasi National award for Economic Journalism in Hindi<ref>{{cite news|url=http://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1300530.cms | title=Rashtriya Arthik Hindi Patrakarita Purskar 2007}}</ref>\n* India's top blogger. Arthaat, a weekly blog in politics and economy, is honoured as one of India's most read in 2016. This ranking is done by the top Indian website on blogging.<ref name=\"bestblogs\">{{cite news|url=http://samachar4media.com/list-of-best-hindi-blogs | title=\u091f\u0949\u092a \u092c\u094d\u0932\u0949\u0917\u094d\u0938 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 \u0939\u0941\u0906 \u0907\u0938 \u0935\u0930\u093f\u0937\u094d\u0920 \u092a\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0915\u093e\u0930 \u0914\u0930 \u0938\u0902\u092a\u093e\u0926\u0915 \u0915\u093e \u0932\u094b\u0915\u092a\u094d\u0930\u093f\u092f \u092c\u094d\u0932\u0949\u0917 2015\u20132016}}</ref>\n\n==Books and publications==\n\n* Research paper on the conundrum of online comments, ''How to get most out of wise crowd'', from [[University of Westminster]] under Chevening Fellowship<ref name=\"chevening\" /> \n* Paper on terrorism and economy, published from Calcutta University\n* Paper \u2013 ''Economic Impact of Terror on South Asia''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://iprovok.com/bomb-and-the-bill-economic-impact-of-terrorism/ | title=Economic Impact of Terrorism: Case of South Asia Post 9/11}}</ref>\n* Paper on India and China relations published from ISAS Singapore; profile carried in the collection of seminal papers<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newasiabooks.org/publication/media-work-china-and-india-discovering-and-dissecting | title=India and China relations published from ISAS Singapore}}</ref>\n* Collection of columns published in Hindi\n* Book on India's economic history is in process\n* Laxminama \u2013 Book launched in November 2018\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.exchange4media.com/print/veteran-journalist-anshuman-tiwari-to-be-new-editor-of-india-today-(hindi)_56778.html Veteran journalist Anshuman Tiwari to be new Editor of India Today (Hindi)- Author, Abhishek Mehrotra, Friday, 1 August 2014]\n* [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/Dainik-Jagran-chief-of-national-bureau-Anshuman-Tiwari-says-that-there-is-need-for-strong-regulation-for-corporate-governance-not-broadcast-regulation-/articleshow/19742129.cms Dainik Jagran chief of national bureau Anshuman Tiwari says that there is need for strong regulation for corporate governance not broadcast regulation]\n* [http://i